      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T21:32:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not the faster-to-market solution. It\u0027s more like a server-side issue instead of a client side. The `prpc.Client` has the automatic retry mechanism on transient grpc codes. So the server side should return correct grpc code. If we don\u0027t change it in BB and only change the bb cli logic, other clients who use BB will face the same issue.\n\nMoreover, I\u0027m thinking if we make the Go BB have the same behaviors as the Py BB, it won\u0027t become worse to our customers at least.",
      "parentUuid": "dd6d3e0b_0386e629",
      "revId": "33eee3c40c28987352f23eb6ebbc9dce6b3a6344",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
