      "writtenOn": "2021-02-05T04:30:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "tbh, I see little value in returning per-op errors iff Py gave top level error.\n\nThe only value I see is iff Go ops succeeded, s.t. we provide partial response.\nHowever, not doing this is strictly not worse than Py version before. \nSo, I recommend to translate top level Py error to top level Go Batch error always:\n + simpler\n + covers transport error case (see below comment)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 124,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 132,
        "endChar": 3
      },
      "revId": "33eee3c40c28987352f23eb6ebbc9dce6b3a6344",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
